  "copy": {
    "caption": "The brave little fish that lives inside a sea of stingers.",
    "shortDescription": "Clownfish live inside sea anemones whose tentacles would sting any other fish to death — but clownfish are covered in a special mucus that tricks the anemone into thinking they're part of itself. They keep the anemone clean by eating parasites and debris, and the anemone keeps predators away. Fun fact: All clownfish are born male — the biggest one in a group can turn female whenever the group needs a female."
